{{Refimprove|date=October 2008}} {{Infobox TV channel | name = Corazon Albiverde | logosize = | logofile = | launch = 17 August 2009 | closed date = | share = N/A | share as of = No data available | share source = | owner = [[Oriente Petrolero]] | former names = | replaced names = | web = [http://www.orienteblog.com/ www.Orienteblog.com] | availability note= | terr serv 1 = | terr chan 1 = | terr serv 2 = | terr chan 2 = | sat serv 1 = [[Facetas Television|Facetas Tv]] | sat chan 1 = Channel 21 | sat serv 2 = [[Tv Cable Analógico]] | sat chan 2 = Channel 2 | sat serv 3 = | sat chan 3 = | cable serv 1 = [[Cotas Cable Digital]] | cable chan 1 = Channel 34 | adsl serv 1 = | adsl chan 1 = | adsl serv 2 = | adsl chan 2 = | adsl serv 3 = | adsl chan 3 = | adsl serv 4 = | adsl chan 4 = | online serv 1 = Yalp.alice.it | online chan 1 = [http://www.justin.tv/corazonalbiverd Live Streaming] | dummy parameter = }}
'''Corazon Albiverde''' is a Bolivian subscription based sports television channel, dedicated to the fans of the Liga del Futbol Professional Boliviano, Oriente Petrolero. The channel first launched in August 2009 on Facetas Tv. The station is registered with Entel as Oriente Digital Media Ltd. It broadcasts daily from 1 pm to 2 pm.
==Presenters== The channel has various [[television presenter|presenters]], Yanine Paniagua Varani known as "La Flaca", Karlos Alberto Espada as "El Pollo".
