{{nihongo|'''''Tokyo Afterschool Summoners'''''|東京放課後サモナーズ|Tōkyō Hōkago Samonāzu|Romusha lead=yes}}, known colloquially by the [[blend word]] {{nihongo|'''''Housamo'''''|放サモ}}, is a [[role-playing video game]] for [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]]. It is developed by {{ill|Lifewonders, LLC){{!}}Lifewonders|ja|四畳半的生活}}, a [[mobile gaming]] company operated by the [[dōjin circle]] {{ill|Yojouhan-teki Seikatsu){{!}}Yojouhan-teki Seikatsu|ja|四畳半的生活}}.<ref name="Circle" /> It is noted as one of the first commercially-produced [[LGBT]] video games created in Japan,<ref name="IGN" /> and one of the first commercially-produced LGBT games to extensively utilize [[gay manga]] ("bara") artwork.<ref name="Buzzap" />

==Gameplay==
''Tokyo Afterschool Summoners'' is a [[free-to-play]] card-based [[role-playing video game]] with [[turn-based]] battles. Each character card has a weapon type, as well as a elemental attribute that determines its strengths and weaknesses against other cards in [[rock–paper–scissors]]-style match-ups. Cards gain levels and abilities by accruing experience through battles; once a card reaches its level cap, special items must be used to uncap the card so it can gain more experience. The game utilizes an affinity system wherein [[Game_balance#Buff|buffs]] are applied when the cards of characters who have a relationship ("love", "like", "dislike", and "rival") are used in battle together. Cards are obtained through quests, or through the game's [[Gacha game|gacha]] system.

==Development==
{{Expand section|date=November 2018}}
The game was released on the [[App Store (iOS)|App Store]] for [[iOS]] on December 2nd, 2016, and on [[Google Play]] for [[Android (operating system)|Android]] on December 16th, 2016. Partial support for the game in [[English language|English]], [[Traditional Chinese]], and [[Simplified Chinese]] was added in March 2018.<ref name="2ndYear" />

==Synopsis==
The protagonist awakens in a version of [[Tokyo]] where "transients" – supernatural beings from fantasy and mythology – live among humans. In this world, both humans and transients utilize mysterious artifacts to fight in duels; duelists organize into [[guild]]s, which fight for control of the 23 [[special wards of Tokyo]]. The player controls the protagonist as they form a guild of their own, gather companions, and attempt to uncover how they have arrived in this world.

==Characters==
===Main characters===
; {{nihongo|Hero}}
: Voiced by: [[Kappei Yamaguchi]] / [[Naoko Matsui]] / [[Toshiyuki Hosaka]] / [[Fuji Aki]] / [[Toshimitsu Oda]]<ref name="HeroVA"/>
: The protagonist of the game. Their name, appearance, voice, and [[gender identity]] are chosen by the player and can be changed at any time.

; {{nihongo|Lil' Salomon|サロモンくん|Salomon-kun}}
:{{voiced by|Kappei Yamaguchi}}
: A [[satyr]] who serves as the hero's [[Familiar spirit|familiar]], and explains the mechanics of the game.

; {{nihongo|Shiro|本居 シロウ|Motoori Shiro}}
:{{voiced by|[[Masaki Yoshida]]}}
: The protagonist's [[class president|class representative]] who is childhood friends with Kengo.

; {{nihongo|Ryota|薬師丸 リョウタ|Yakushimaru Ryota}}
:{{voiced by|[[Yoshihito Oomami]]}}
: A laid-back and jovial classmate to the hero and Shiro.

; {{nihongo|Kengo|高伏 ケンゴ|Takafushi Kengo}}
:{{voiced by|[[Yuhei Iwanaga]]}}
: A childhood friend to Shiro, though their friendship has fractured due to Kengo's [[truancy]].

; {{nihongo|Toji|崎守 トウジ|Sakimori Toji}}
:{{voiced by|[[Koji Marunaka]]}}
: An apprentice ''[[kannushi]]'' and demon hunter.

===Secondary characters===
; {{nihongo|[[Ægir|Aegir]]|エーギル}}
:{{voiced by|[[Hisao Egawa]]}}
: A [[giant]] transient and treasure hunter.

; {{nihongo|[[Captain Ahab|Ahab]]|エイハブ}}
:{{voiced by|[[Unshō Ishizuka]]}}
: A [[Furry fandom|anthropomorphic water buffalo]] transient and [[whaler]].

; {{nihongo|[[Amir Arsalan|Arslan]]|アルスラーン}}
:{{voiced by|[[Kenichi Ogata (voice actor)|Kenichi Ogata]]}}
: An anthropomorphic lion transient and [[Oil wrestling|oil wrestler]] who is the guardian of the Aoyama guild.

; {{nihongo|[[Azazel]]|アザゼル}}
:{{voiced by|[[Junya Inaba]]}}
: An anthropomorphic goat transient and member of the Aoyma guild.

; {{nihongo|[[Benzaiten|Benten]]|ベンテン}}
:{{voiced by|[[Haruna Ikezawa]]}}
: A transient high school girl and [[biwa]] player.

; {{nihongo|Choji|チョウジ}}
:{{voiced by|[[Masato Yoshida]]}}
: A member of the cooking club at the protagonist's school who wields the [[Apicius]] as his artifact.

; {{nihongo|Hakumen|ハクメン}}
:{{voiced by|[[Yumiko Kobayashi]]}}
: A [[kitsune]] transient who owns a casino in Tokyo.

; {{nihongo|[[Kamuy|Horkeu Kamui]]|ホロケウカムイ}}
:{{voiced by|Masato Yoshida}}
: A anthropomorphic [[Hokkaido wolf]] transient  and member of the Ikebukuro Berserkers.

; {{nihongo|[[Fūma Kotarō|Kotaro]]|風間 コタロウ|Kazama Kotaro}}
:{{voiced by|[[Orie Kimoto]]}}
: A [[boy genius]] and [[ninja]] who is a classmate to the hero.

; {{nihongo|[[Lucifuge Rofocale|Lucifuge]]|ルキフゲ}}
:{{voiced by|[[Takashi Yonezawa]]}}
: A transient and executive of the Roppongi Tycoons crime syndicate.

; {{nihongo|Maria|マリア}}
:{{voiced by|Orie Kimoto}}
: A [[nun]] who serves as the acting master of the [[Aoyama, Minato, Tokyo|Aoyama]] guild.

; {{nihongo|[[Nansō Satomi Hakkenden|Moritaka]]|犬塚 モリタカ|Inuka Moritaka}}
:{{voiced by|Kappei Yamaguchi}}
: A anthropomorphic dog transient and classmate to the hero.

; {{nihongo|[[Nyarlathotep]]|ニャルラトテプ}}
:{{voiced by|Junya Inaba}}
: An anthropomorphic hyena transient  and DJ.

; {{nihongo|[[Ophion]]|オピオーン}}
:{{voiced by|[[Jōji Nakata]]}}
: A transient [[dragon]] and executive of the Roppongi Tycoons.

; {{nihongo|[[Typhon]]|テュポーン}}
:{{voiced by|[[Wataru Takagi]]}}
: A anthropomorphic shark transient and surfer.

; {{nihongo|[[Zabaniyya|Zabaniya]]|ザバーニーヤ}}
:{{voiced by|[[Hiroaki Hirata]]}}
: A transient and member of the Aoyma guild who specializes in torture.

